An unidentified man died in an early morning lone accident that occurred in Osogbo, the Osun State capital, on Monday. It was gathered that the accident, which involved a motorcycle, happened around 6:50 am around Osogbo-Ikirun road, Lameco roundabout, Osogbo. The crash, according to the Sector Public Education Officer for Osun Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Agnes Ogungbemi, might have been caused by speed violation. One dead, two injured in Lagos-Ibadan expressway accident She said that the phone of the deceased and the motorcycle involved in the crash was brought to the FRSC base in Osun State. “Phone and the motorcycle involved in the crash was brought to base while the corpse was deposited at UNIOSUN Teaching Hospital mortuary,” she said. Man dead, eight injured in Osun lone accident